<p>14th-Wednesday-June - <br/>Raining heavily. Much shelling on front &amp; second line.</p>
<p>15th. Thursday.<br/>Very cold weather much fatigue &amp; shelling by both sides. great airial activity.</p>
<p>16th. Friday.<br/>Weather good usual fatigues &amp; airial activity.</p>
<p>17th. Saturday.<br/>Relieved by 19th Battn. only to go on engineers fatigue till 11pm.</p>
<p>18th. Sunday. Slept in till 10am. Church service in billet evening. Our artillery gave enemy trenches lots later.</p>
<p>19th. Monday.<br/>Dull day. Hot bath after dinner. Truck fatigue</p>
